title: For Sale:  Palmetto State Armory Premium M4 AR15 5.56 NATO in Burnt Bronze with Eotech
postcontent:
This is a new in the box rifle with custom Cerakote work professionally applied by Coyote Rifleworks in Houston, TX.

It began as a Palmetto State Armory Premium M4 and was upgraded to the following specs:

5.56 NATO
1/7 twist
Chrome Moly Vanadium barrel
Forged 7075-T6 upper and lower receiver
Dust cover
Forward assist
Full auto bolt carrier group
Dry film lubricated buffer tube
Combat trigger group
Midwest Industries aluminum quad rail
30 round magazine
Vertical grip with spring loaded bipod
Eotech 512.A65 holographic red dot sight

The entire rifle has been had a high temperature ceramic Cerakote finish applied to it - all of the polymer (plastic) pieces, the roll pins, controls (mag release, bolt release, safety, take down pins, etc) barrel, buffer tube, magazine, front sight, and gas block have been done in Graphite Black.

The upper and lower receiver, and the hood of the Eotech have been done in Burnt Bronze. This is my absolute favorite color finish that Cerakote provides. It is so difficult to capture the life in the color with a camera - the same way I imagine a jeweler has a difficult time photographing a diamond. In direct sunlight this gun really pops!

The Cerakote finish is the best available on the market for protection from corrosion and the elements as well as superior resistance to wear and use. You would really have to abuse your rifle in order to damage this finish.

As for the quality of Palmetto State Armory, I'd put it just above top echelon Colts and Rock River Arms - far, far above DPMS, Bushmaster, Windham, and other entry AR manufacturers. Their attention to detail in the quality of their build and refusal to allow anything with a blemish to enter the market is second to none.

My price is $1600 (LOWERED FROM $1800, retail price of over $2000) for the rifle and the optic. I am not interested in any trades and will not part out the rifle or sell without the Eotech.

You can contact me directly at REDACTED if you have any questions.
